  "body": "### Description\n\nQuarkus can read from different Config Sources, yet the format is generally of two forms: properties and environment variables.\r\n\r\nThe conversion of properties to environment variables is mostly straightforward, but anyway it would be nice to have in the documentation the environment variable alternative form to have easy access to the correct name.\r\n\r\nAlso when searching, allow searching from the env var name too.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nOption 1: show in the description as a piece of extra information.\r\n```\r\nquarkus.datasource.jdbc.initial-size\r\n\r\nThe initial size of the pool. Usually you will want to set the initial size...\r\n\r\nEnvironment variable: QUARKUS_DATASOURCE_JDBC_INITIAL_SIZE\r\n```\r\n\r\nOption 2: show on the side of the property\r\n```\r\nquarkus.datasource.jdbc.min-size / QUARKUS_DATASOURCE_JDBC_MIN_SIZE\r\n\r\nThe datasource pool minimum size\r\n```\r\n\r\nI honestly prefer option 1 with the same style as the title `<code>QUARKUS_DATASOURCE_JDBC_INITIAL_SIZE</code>` but whatever is chosen would be fine.",
